00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:18,030
Yeah.

223
00:12:18,330 --> 00:12:20,930
In the beginning
they called me to invite me.

224
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:22,970
When I refused, the thugs came.

225
00:12:23,649 --> 00:12:26,329
I told 'em to look people in the eye
when talking and threw 'em out.

226
00:12:26,530 --> 00:12:28,662
And here we are today.

227
00:12:28,762 --> 00:12:30,482
You didn't report it
to the police, did you?

228
00:12:31,076 --> 00:12:33,050
Yeah, I thought about that.

229
00:12:33,897 --> 00:12:38,233
But if the cops are there all
day long, no customers will come.

230
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,000
They predicted
that much, all right.

231
00:12:41,116 --> 00:12:43,086
Do you know which group
the thugs belonged to?

232
00:12:44,410 --> 00:12:47,250
They belong to the Takeda
family down the street.

233
00:12:47,570 --> 00:12:51,357
I think Sanritsu Industries is the
mastermind behind the protection racket.

234
00:12:53,830 --> 00:12:55,575
I heard that the
Takeda family's boss

235
00:12:55,599 --> 00:12:58,180
became a shareholder of
Sanritsu Industries the other day.

236
00:12:59,430 --> 00:13:01,533
I think that's fishy.

237
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:03,160
I didn't know that.

238
00:13:06,533 --> 00:13:07,557
A champion, huh?

239
00:13:08,430 --> 00:13:11,940
Well, I'm past my prime if
I'm remembering the old days.

240
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:31,900
Welcome back!

241
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:34,630
Oh...

242
00:13:34,981 --> 00:13:36,489
- What happened to your car?
- Uhâ¦

243
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:40,320
What happened to the drivers?

244
00:13:41,310 --> 00:13:42,310
Wellâ¦

245
00:13:42,580 --> 00:13:43,580
Did they all quit?

246
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:45,260
Yes.

247
00:13:46,410 --> 00:13:48,480
But that's okay.
Hire someone new again.

248
00:13:49,810 --> 00:13:51,070
Maybe I should learn to drive.

249
00:13:56,310 --> 00:13:57,600
What about tomorrow's work?

250
00:13:58,910 --> 00:14:00,194
I turned it down earlier.

251
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,131
I'm sure it's not a good time.

252
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:11,950
Come on! Tonight is Osamu's
welcome home party.

253
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:13,790
It's going to be
at my apartment.

254
00:14:16,740 --> 00:14:18,530
- Osamu?
- What's wrong?

255
00:14:21,410 --> 00:14:24,308
I showed those guys from the Takeda
family how strong I got in juvie.

256
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,738
Idiot! What would you do if
something happened to you?

257
00:14:27,863 --> 00:14:30,458
Worry more about yourself
than you do about me!

258
00:14:31,648 --> 00:14:34,578
- Osamu, what happened?
- Ouch!

259
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,080
Captain Fujikawa was
happy that you agreed.

260
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,640
We'll help as much as we can.

261
00:14:47,712 --> 00:14:51,500
But this work is informal.

262
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,500
Yes.

263
00:14:52,660 --> 00:14:55,840
So it's strange when I'm the
one asking you to do this, but

264
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:57,760
- you take good care of yourself and--
- Old man.

265
00:14:58,570 --> 00:14:59,930
You needn't worry about that.

266
00:15:00,655 --> 00:15:03,062
I'm willing to do it even
if no one asks me to do it.

267
00:15:03,671 --> 00:15:05,591
Well, I feel better now
that you put it that way.

268
00:15:06,093 --> 00:15:07,413
And what about your subordinates?

269
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:09,977
I want to work in my own way,

270
00:15:10,341 --> 00:15:12,781
so I'm going to get five or six
guys who are used to fighting.

271
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:15,330
What I'd really like from you
is a car that starts fast.

272
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:17,060
I've already got it for you.

273
00:15:17,488 --> 00:15:18,830
I've got a good driver too.

274
00:15:19,070 --> 00:15:20,503
- Come with me now.
- Okay.

275
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,330
Why did we stop here?

276
00:15:40,220 --> 00:15:42,140
Well, wait and see.
He'll appear any moment.

277
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,600
Huh?

278
00:16:03,950 --> 00:16:04,950
Matsushima!

279
00:16:07,496 --> 00:16:09,440
Hey, you're caught red-handed.

280
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,100
I haven't done it yet.

281
00:16:12,425 --> 00:16:13,665
You should be glad you haven't.

282
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:16,360
If you had, you'd be back
eating stinky food in jail.

283
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:18,300
Sorry.

284
00:16:18,403 --> 00:16:21,215
I'll tell you what, instead, I'm
going to have a little chat with you.

285
00:16:21,380 --> 00:16:22,603
Please, no more lectures--

286
00:16:22,628 --> 00:16:23,867
That's not what I meant.

287
00:16:24,062 --> 00:16:25,950
- I want to show you something.
- Huh?

288
00:16:28,667 --> 00:16:29,858
Whoa!

289
00:16:30,442 --> 00:16:31,890
This engine--
It's like a sports car!

290
00:16:32,169 --> 00:16:33,969
What do you think?
Would you like to drive it?

291
00:16:33,969 --> 00:16:35,096
Oh? You don't mind?

292
00:16:35,313 --> 00:16:37,008
- I'll leave it with you.
- Yeah!

293
00:16:49,390 --> 00:16:50,650
Oh, it's a police motorcycle.

294
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:52,730
- Should we make a run for it?
- Idiot!

295
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:55,847
You should stop
for the poor guy.

296
00:16:56,430 --> 00:16:57,430
Are you sure?

297
00:17:11,570 --> 00:17:13,330
Do you know how fast
you were going just now?

298
00:17:15,150 --> 00:17:17,310
Thank you for your work,
but there's a reason for that.

299
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:18,310
Are you on a case?

300
00:17:18,430 --> 00:17:20,175
Yes, well, something like that.

301
00:17:20,175 --> 00:17:21,815
Sorry about that.
Thank you for your work.

302
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:24,380
This is great!
Shall we try a little more?

303
00:17:25,150 --> 00:17:27,260
I've had enough of this.
I'll turn it down this time.

304
00:17:28,009 --> 00:17:30,167
I'll introduce you to
a guy you might like. Go!

305
00:17:31,497 --> 00:17:32,497
You damned fool!

306
00:17:33,570 --> 00:17:35,610
What the hell are you doing?
Fuck you, motherfucker!

307
00:17:35,787 --> 00:17:36,787
Come here!

308
00:17:36,812 --> 00:17:38,330
Get the fuck off me!

309
00:17:38,330 --> 00:17:40,390
You son of a bitch!
You ruined a girl's life!

310
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:43,520
Get the fuck off me!
Get off of me!

311
00:17:44,101 --> 00:17:45,164
- What's going on?
- Oh...

312
00:17:45,274 --> 00:17:46,855
He tricked a runaway
girl and sold her.

313
00:17:46,855 --> 00:17:47,855
Oh.

314
00:17:48,426 --> 00:17:50,496
Well, that's the guy.

315
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:54,199
He's so hot-blooded that he
sometimes forgets his duties.

316
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:57,370
But he's a great shot.
I'll introduce you.

317
00:17:57,970 --> 00:17:59,122
- Excuse me.
- Oh!

318
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:00,960
What are you doing?

319
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:03,489
- I see, he's fast--
- Drop the gun!

320
00:18:04,035 --> 00:18:05,035
Oh, excuse me.

321
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:07,560
Mr. Ogata asked me
to test your skills.

322
00:18:08,140 --> 00:18:10,180
Sorry, sorry.
This man is right.

323
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:14,196
Never trust a person
who has a gun.

324
00:18:15,245 --> 00:18:17,365
By the time you get mad
at their trick, it's too late.

325
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:23,792
Okay. Old man,
you should explain.

326
00:18:24,253 --> 00:18:25,792
- I have some other ideas.
- Okay.

327
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:38,350
Ron.

328
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:43,413
There you go.

329
00:18:49,764 --> 00:18:50,764
Ron.

330
00:18:52,014 --> 00:18:53,655
- Here, reach!
- Ron!

331
00:18:55,233 --> 00:18:57,070
Little three dragons. Half flash.

332
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:58,165
You bastard!

333
00:19:00,355 --> 00:19:01,355
You son of a bitch!

334
00:19:13,290 --> 00:19:14,290
Bro!

335
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:17,311
I don't know what all this is about,
but give him a break.

336
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:18,570
I'm telling you--

337
00:19:24,919 --> 00:19:26,653
Let's go. Come on.

338
00:19:29,607 --> 00:19:33,170
Man! Thanks for saving me. I guess
it's different when you're a pro.

339
00:19:33,170 --> 00:19:35,570
Don't you have any shame,
cheating a bunch of thugs?

340
00:19:35,570 --> 00:19:37,650
Well, it's like they say,
"Poverty dulls the spirit."

341
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:39,180
What's up?

342
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:40,629
I need to borrow your help.

343
00:19:40,990 --> 00:19:41,990
It's work, isn't it?

344
00:19:43,660 --> 00:19:45,250
Is it a safe or is it a--

345
00:19:45,324 --> 00:19:47,580
Neither. Anyway, come
to my house tonight.

346
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:54,820
If you want the manager,
he ain't here!

347
00:19:56,423 --> 00:19:58,876
The owner changed today.

348
00:19:59,470 --> 00:20:01,060
Go there to collect the debt!

349
00:20:01,354 --> 00:20:03,034
Looks like things are
pretty rough for you.

350
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:06,174
Boss. You've come
at a good time.

351
00:20:07,150 --> 00:20:10,206
I'm not sure I'd enjoy a
farewell party by myself.

352
00:20:10,340 --> 00:20:11,456
What farewell party?

353
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,690
They're all gone.

354
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:17,750
How did that happen?

355
00:20:19,230 --> 00:20:20,230
Well...

356
00:20:20,550 --> 00:20:22,550
A series of disturbances
the other night, you know,

357
00:20:22,843 --> 00:20:24,913
bartenders running away,
waitresses being takenâ¦

358
00:20:26,020 --> 00:20:30,140
Even the debt was taken
over by Sanritsu Industries.

359
00:20:31,987 --> 00:20:33,627
The former champion
is no longer in shape!

360
00:20:35,950 --> 00:20:37,868
I'll give them all to that
bastard Tatsumura!

361
00:20:39,587 --> 00:20:42,282
I'll explain later, but I want
you to come to my place tonight.

362
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:46,340
Hey, sis! My brother's back!

363
00:20:49,085 --> 00:20:51,425
Honey, those people have
come to pick up the truck.

364
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:52,600
Did you really sell it?

365
00:20:52,679 --> 00:20:54,079
Yeah, we've already
made the deal.

366
00:20:54,370 --> 00:20:55,400
Please take it!

367
00:20:57,760 --> 00:21:00,210
Hey, why are you doing this?
What are we going to do now?

368
00:21:01,076 --> 00:21:02,236
I'm sorry to break it to you,

369
00:21:02,412 --> 00:21:04,544
but I've decided to
go back to my old life.

370
00:21:05,060 --> 00:21:06,060
What?

371
00:21:06,290 --> 00:21:08,210
You'll have to live in the
apartment for a while.

372
00:21:08,860 --> 00:21:09,900
That's the brother I know!

373
00:21:10,082 --> 00:21:13,199
Sorry, but there's a world of men that
women don't understand. Right, bro?

374
00:21:13,457 --> 00:21:16,316
You go live with her.
And get a job.

375
00:21:16,540 --> 00:21:17,763
That's stupid!

376
00:21:18,090 --> 00:21:19,870
Please, please don't do it.

377
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:21,750
Did you forget what
happened four years ago?

378
00:21:21,776 --> 00:21:24,174
Didn't you almost die trying
to crawl out of the muck?

379
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:27,120
Don't get desperate just because
things aren't working here.

380
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,500
We can go somewhere
where there are no yakuza.

381
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:32,393
Please, please don't do it.

382
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:35,294
I'm sorry, but I've
made up my mind.

383
00:21:36,190 --> 00:21:37,590
This time I'm going
to do it my way.

384
00:21:37,815 --> 00:21:39,215
That's right!
That's right, brother!

385
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:42,127
But you can't do it alone, bro.
Hey, please, let me do it.

386
00:21:42,230 --> 00:21:43,550
I'll bring my friends
if you want.

387
00:21:43,919 --> 00:21:44,919
Idiot!

388
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:48,360
I said no, you can't do it.

389
00:21:49,724 --> 00:21:50,890
Pack your bags with her.

390
00:21:55,748 --> 00:21:57,443
I've now given you
the gist of it.

391
00:21:57,693 --> 00:21:59,213
I'd really like some
help from you all.

392
00:21:59,784 --> 00:22:02,455
I just want to assure you that
we're subcontracting for the police.

393
00:22:02,770 --> 00:22:03,970
It's low-pay despite the risk.

394
00:22:04,890 --> 00:22:07,050
I'd like to know if you're
still willing to take it on.

395
00:22:07,090 --> 00:22:08,370
Please don't
hesitate to tell me.

396
00:22:08,820 --> 00:22:11,624
When you say subcontracting for
the police, how will you start?

397
00:22:12,470 --> 00:22:15,260
First I'll pretend to make
a comeback to the yakuza.

398
00:22:15,650 --> 00:22:19,392
Then I'll infiltrate their organization
under the guise of a turf war.

399
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:22,193
That would mean
we're the Tojima family.

400
00:22:22,218 --> 00:22:23,938
Gentlemen, this is the
perfect role for you.

401
00:22:24,420 --> 00:22:26,660
If you look in the mirror
I think you'll see what I mean.

402
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,770
I don't want to flatter you, but
I'd hardly call you all good citizens.

403
00:22:33,972 --> 00:22:37,761
But it takes a hell of a lot of
guts and horsepower to hit them.

404
00:22:39,830 --> 00:22:41,670
You're all perfect team
members in that regard.

405
00:22:42,230 --> 00:22:45,716
Hey, bro, even though it's police work,
we're putting our lives on the line.

406
00:22:46,810 --> 00:22:48,490
There will be a little
reward, won't there?

407
00:22:48,490 --> 00:22:49,812
I can't guarantee that.

408
00:22:50,351 --> 00:22:52,210
I'm sure you'll
manage it just fine.

409
00:22:54,050 --> 00:22:56,534
But don't forget there's
a policeman next to you.

410
00:23:00,527 --> 00:23:02,214
So let's hear your answer.

411
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:04,816
Can you guys give me a hand?

412
00:23:05,190 --> 00:23:06,590
Let's show them what we can do!

413
00:23:07,135 --> 00:23:09,095
I'll get Tatsumura back
for his protection racket.

414
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:10,360
How about you, Matsushima?

415
00:23:11,020 --> 00:23:12,820
Well, I'm being asked
to take care of the car.

416
00:23:13,258 --> 00:23:15,040
I don't see anyone
else qualified.

417
00:23:15,130 --> 00:23:16,130
Goro?

418
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,972
I'll do my best to
save the extra money.

419
00:23:19,107 --> 00:23:20,107
Mr. policeman?

420
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:21,722
It's my duty so
I'll do whatever--

421
00:23:27,339 --> 00:23:28,339
You scared me!

422
00:23:28,511 --> 00:23:29,642
- Osamu!
- Brother...

423
00:23:29,667 --> 00:23:30,907
Don't treat me like a stranger!

424
00:23:31,589 --> 00:23:33,495
Everyone, I'm his
brother, Osamu Kaji.

425
00:23:33,675 --> 00:23:35,072
We're actually half-siblings.

426
00:23:35,447 --> 00:23:36,647
How many times
have I told you?

427
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:38,229
I'm not gonna
make you one of us.

428
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,870
Again with that.
I wish you'd trust me.

429
00:23:41,870 --> 00:23:43,990
But a goofball like you
would be the first to get hit.

430
00:23:44,535 --> 00:23:45,975
I can't take care
of a guy like that.

431
00:23:46,004 --> 00:23:47,770
Well, then, brother.
You mean you can't--

432
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:49,400
You'd be slowing me down.
Give it up.

433
00:23:49,717 --> 00:23:52,131
Fine, then!
I'll do my own thing!

434
00:23:52,413 --> 00:23:53,835
Osamu... Osamu!

435
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:58,750
He's just like you the way he won't
back out of something once he's said it.

436
00:23:59,537 --> 00:24:00,657
He's a real pain in the ass.

437
00:24:02,008 --> 00:24:03,400
So everything is
okay then, right?

438
00:24:04,540 --> 00:24:06,203
Okay, now let's get to work.

439
00:24:06,840 --> 00:24:09,660
First you'll go out and spread word
that I'm making a comeback.

