480
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:48,500
Who are you?

481
00:27:48,855 --> 00:27:50,253
You almost got yourself killed.

482
00:27:51,767 --> 00:27:53,047
Do you know what's
going on here?

483
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:56,000
I do, but thanks anyway.

484
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:57,600
Don't get me wrong.

485
00:27:58,334 --> 00:28:00,928
I'm here to kill you.
Don't move!

486
00:28:03,553 --> 00:28:04,928
Do you recognize this face?

487
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:06,680
Five years agoâ¦

488
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:08,480
Five years ago?

489
00:28:09,116 --> 00:28:11,600
In a turf war on the beach,
you shot a guy named Kuroki.

490
00:28:12,180 --> 00:28:14,880
Then you're Kuroki's--

491
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:15,880
I'm his younger brother.

492
00:28:16,540 --> 00:28:18,300
Now that you remember,
I'm going to kill you.

493
00:28:18,300 --> 00:28:19,300
Wait!

494
00:28:20,100 --> 00:28:21,740
That wasn't supposed
to be a fatal injury.

495
00:28:21,740 --> 00:28:23,700
No respectable doctor
would've treated that wound.

496
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:25,730
It's no wonder it was fatal.

497
00:28:26,594 --> 00:28:27,774
I made a vow then.

498
00:28:28,510 --> 00:28:30,235
I swore I'd kill you
if I ever saw you!

499
00:28:35,094 --> 00:28:36,094
Are you hurt?

500
00:28:36,365 --> 00:28:37,365
You think you saved me?

501
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:39,602
That doesn't make up
for my brother!

502
00:28:40,100 --> 00:28:41,100
Wait a minute!

503
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:53,380
I get how you feel, but
I've got a job I've got to do.

504
00:28:53,990 --> 00:28:54,990
I won't let you stop me.

505
00:28:55,024 --> 00:28:56,660
- Boss, are you hurt?
- I'm fine.

506
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:59,025
The advertisement worked 100%.

507
00:28:59,025 --> 00:29:00,385
I've already got
a lot of sponsors.

508
00:29:00,750 --> 00:29:01,750
That's the guy.

509
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,320
Him?

510
00:29:04,290 --> 00:29:05,350
A debt is a debt.

511
00:29:05,980 --> 00:29:07,260
I'll wait until
your job is done.

512
00:29:08,197 --> 00:29:10,824
In exchange, I'm not leaving
your side for a while.

513
00:29:11,963 --> 00:29:13,603
I won't let you die
until it's by my hand.

514
00:29:14,029 --> 00:29:16,443
So you're a bodyguard. Well, okay.

515
00:29:17,193 --> 00:29:18,953
He's an old friend of mine.
Try to get along.

516
00:29:19,350 --> 00:29:20,950
Starting tomorrow
we're going to be busy.

517
00:29:37,288 --> 00:29:39,397
SANRITSU INDUSTRIES

518
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:49,679
Boss, Tojima is here.

519
00:29:50,010 --> 00:29:51,010
What do you want to do?

520
00:29:52,150 --> 00:29:53,939
I thought they'd
be here by now.

521
00:30:00,251 --> 00:30:01,251
Hey.

522
00:30:02,642 --> 00:30:04,050
To what do we owe
this surprise?

523
00:30:04,050 --> 00:30:05,050
It's been a while.

524
00:30:06,087 --> 00:30:07,462
How's your shipping
company doing?

525
00:30:08,072 --> 00:30:10,900
I heard you were happy together
with the previous boss's daughter.

526
00:30:10,962 --> 00:30:12,962
I don't think I can make
a living as an honest man.

527
00:30:13,127 --> 00:30:14,939
I'm going back
to the old Tojima.

528
00:30:15,291 --> 00:30:18,150
I see. That's why you came all
the way out here to say hello.

529
00:30:19,330 --> 00:30:21,890
Shimadzu. Let's celebrate
Tojima's comeback.

530
00:30:22,236 --> 00:30:23,316
Book a welcome home party--

531
00:30:23,425 --> 00:30:25,066
You already threw me
a welcome home party.

532
00:30:25,786 --> 00:30:27,161
A fancy one with lead bullets.

533
00:30:28,990 --> 00:30:30,790
I know it was supposed
to be a fireworks show,

534
00:30:31,197 --> 00:30:32,838
but it was very much your style.

535
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:37,460
Tojima....

536
00:30:38,143 --> 00:30:40,229
You've become nastier
living as an honest man.

537
00:30:40,230 --> 00:30:41,560
I'm not as bad as you.

538
00:30:42,961 --> 00:30:45,001
You took over this building
in less than four years?

539
00:30:45,610 --> 00:30:47,383
I was hoping you'd tell me
how to make money.

540
00:30:48,051 --> 00:30:50,575
That's the kind of advice one can
only get from a professional.

541
00:30:51,590 --> 00:30:53,035
I wish you'd stop
with the innuendos.

542
00:30:53,613 --> 00:30:55,543
Sanritsu Industries
is a legitimate company.

543
00:30:55,870 --> 00:30:57,060
And we pay our taxes.

544
00:30:57,725 --> 00:30:59,405
If you want, you can
go ask the tax office.

545
00:30:59,710 --> 00:31:03,140
But I hear there's a lot of money to be
made without the tax office knowing.

546
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:04,600
What do you mean?

547
00:31:04,850 --> 00:31:07,710
For example...
protection rackets.

548
00:31:09,273 --> 00:31:10,843
That sort of work
fits these guys.

549
00:31:12,202 --> 00:31:13,202
Don't move!

550
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:17,240
What's this?

551
00:31:17,470 --> 00:31:18,470
A raccoon dog's tail?

552
00:31:21,450 --> 00:31:23,015
I'm the one who built all this.

553
00:31:24,300 --> 00:31:25,940
I have some allies,
but also many enemies.

554
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:29,436
You can never be too careful.

555
00:31:31,500 --> 00:31:32,500
Everyone, leave us.

556
00:31:37,859 --> 00:31:39,883
I think it's time to
cut to the chase.

557
00:31:41,390 --> 00:31:43,562
I'm being extorted, it seems.

558
00:31:43,699 --> 00:31:46,405
No, I just need a little help.

559
00:31:47,241 --> 00:31:49,577
It's a lot of work to make up
for four years of absence.

560
00:31:50,273 --> 00:31:53,150
I'd like to borrow your territory
for a while, for old time's sake.

561
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:55,800
Sorry, I don't have anything
like that right now.

562
00:31:57,390 --> 00:31:59,944
I have enough to eat running a
theater and a recreation center.

563
00:32:00,100 --> 00:32:02,686
Oh yeah? That's a relief.

564
00:32:03,190 --> 00:32:05,250
Then I'll make my own
territory without reservation.

565
00:32:07,070 --> 00:32:09,484
That's all well and good,
but be careful.

566
00:32:10,190 --> 00:32:13,444
They say once a boxer retires,
he never makes a comeback again.

567
00:32:13,890 --> 00:32:16,160
Jinxes can be broken
someday, you know.

568
00:32:17,312 --> 00:32:19,461
Well, look forward to it.

569
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:23,190
I see.

570
00:32:24,329 --> 00:32:25,802
Tojima has shown up

571
00:32:25,921 --> 00:32:27,970
so now Tatsumura has
more things to worry about.

572
00:32:28,260 --> 00:32:30,600
That's why he tried to
get rid of him last night.

573
00:32:30,620 --> 00:32:32,660
That was a screw-up,
out of character for Tatsumura.

574
00:32:32,990 --> 00:32:34,210
I'm getting lucky.

575
00:32:34,590 --> 00:32:35,870
It's good to live a long time.

576
00:32:36,900 --> 00:32:39,710
You've pit the two against each
other for your own advantage?

577
00:32:41,575 --> 00:32:44,176
I'm the one who originally created
Sanritsu Industries, after all.

578
00:32:44,850 --> 00:32:46,930
I didn't want to keep it in
Tatsumura's care forever.

579
00:32:47,580 --> 00:32:48,580
So...

580
00:32:48,865 --> 00:32:51,905
Shall we propose the election of a new
president at the next general meeting?

581
00:32:52,130 --> 00:32:55,040
No, I think we'll wait
and see what Tojima does.

582
00:32:55,933 --> 00:32:57,214
- Chairman!
- Hmm?

583
00:32:58,777 --> 00:33:00,580
Mr. Tojima has come
to say hello to you.

584
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:03,800
Good thing he came now.

585
00:33:04,390 --> 00:33:05,390
Have him come over here.

586
00:33:14,500 --> 00:33:15,740
Mr. Chairman,
it's been a while.

587
00:33:15,976 --> 00:33:18,176
Yeah, a while. I hear you
made a comeback the other day.

588
00:33:18,340 --> 00:33:20,450
Yeah. I'll need
your help again.

589
00:33:20,565 --> 00:33:21,565
Yeah, sure.

590
00:33:22,110 --> 00:33:24,450
But now I'm
practically retired.

591
00:33:24,810 --> 00:33:25,810
Butâ¦

592
00:33:26,024 --> 00:33:29,340
I heard a rumor that you'll be returning
as president of Sanritsu once again.

593
00:33:30,750 --> 00:33:32,873
There are too many
irresponsible rumors out there.

594
00:33:32,898 --> 00:33:33,898
I agree.

595
00:33:35,050 --> 00:33:37,700
I was even gossiping
with Tatsumura just now.

596
00:33:38,175 --> 00:33:40,990
With Tatsumura? They say
you had a dispute last night.

597
00:33:43,430 --> 00:33:45,310
That's just another
irresponsible rumor.

598
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:49,090
But you better be careful.

599
00:33:49,813 --> 00:33:51,282
It's weird saying this
to your face,

600
00:33:51,790 --> 00:33:54,188
I've always preferred you
to Tatsumura.

601
00:33:55,060 --> 00:33:57,327
If you ever need help,
I'm always here for you.

602
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:59,851
Oh. I'll see you, then.

603
00:34:00,421 --> 00:34:01,920
Well, I'll leave you
alone for today.

604
00:34:05,770 --> 00:34:07,810
This is a fine house
for an old fox's nest.

605
00:34:08,231 --> 00:34:10,031
And they're even planning
to expand the place.

606
00:34:26,976 --> 00:34:30,483
SANRITSU INDUSTRIES

607
00:34:31,060 --> 00:34:34,400
I see. That old man
and Tojima, huh?

608
00:34:35,060 --> 00:34:37,813
I think we can still do
something about it now.

609
00:34:40,740 --> 00:34:42,020
You're something yourself too.

610
00:34:42,820 --> 00:34:43,820
What are you after?

611
00:34:44,335 --> 00:34:45,570
The Sakura family's territory?

612
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:49,150
Well, if that's on the table.

613
00:34:52,410 --> 00:34:53,410
Okay.

614
00:34:53,790 --> 00:34:54,790
I'll grant you that.

615
00:34:55,580 --> 00:34:56,720
In exchange, get to work.

616
00:34:58,910 --> 00:34:59,910
Eliminate the old man.

617
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:02,120
Boss.

618
00:35:02,510 --> 00:35:03,740
He's your blood relative.

619
00:35:04,945 --> 00:35:06,625
I don't remember having
an uncle like that.

620
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:08,480
Murakami.

621
00:35:08,910 --> 00:35:09,980
Take the Kijima brothers.

622
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:16,600
Mr. Chairman.

623
00:35:19,431 --> 00:35:22,050
These men say that they
came from Tatsumura.

624
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:23,600
What do they want?

625
00:35:23,821 --> 00:35:24,981
Can't you handle it yourself?

626
00:35:24,981 --> 00:35:26,371
No, I definitely can't.

627
00:35:29,216 --> 00:35:30,787
What are you doing?
Stop it, you!

628
00:35:48,789 --> 00:35:52,815
CHAIRMAN OF SANRITSU
INDUSTRIES MURDERED

629
00:35:53,886 --> 00:35:55,246
Killing anyone who
gets in the way?

630
00:35:55,589 --> 00:35:56,964
But this is too much!

631
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,870
This is exactly how
Tatsumura works.

632
00:36:00,260 --> 00:36:02,266
Now their organization
is strengthened again.

633
00:36:04,750 --> 00:36:07,000
We have to find a
new way to get inside.

634
00:36:14,735 --> 00:36:16,102
Welcome. Can I
get you a drink?

635
00:36:17,220 --> 00:36:19,360
I don't have any money.
Here, let me pay with this.

636
00:36:21,516 --> 00:36:23,657
We're supposed to ask for cash.

637
00:36:24,290 --> 00:36:25,400
Don't be so uptight.

638
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:26,930
I heard whose
restaurant this is.

639
00:36:33,660 --> 00:36:34,660
Welcome.

640
00:36:36,150 --> 00:36:37,150
Eh?

641
00:36:37,418 --> 00:36:38,858
Are you the one
I need to talk to?

642
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:40,480
Maybe. We'll see.

643
00:36:41,130 --> 00:36:42,130
Boy, where are you from?

644
00:36:43,305 --> 00:36:45,206
Check the family register.
No comment.

645
00:36:45,315 --> 00:36:46,593
Well?! I want a clear answer!

646
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:48,160
Come this way.

647
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:55,670
Here.

648
00:36:56,722 --> 00:36:57,722
The pistol.

649
00:36:59,100 --> 00:37:00,100
Wait here.

650
00:37:01,832 --> 00:37:03,897
MANAGER'S OFFICE

651
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:07,004
I have someone
we could use.

652
00:37:13,740 --> 00:37:14,740
We heard your story.

653
00:37:14,987 --> 00:37:16,814
- Go home for today.
- What?

654
00:37:16,850 --> 00:37:19,310
We have to check if the gun
has been used in a crime.

655
00:37:19,733 --> 00:37:22,360
If you can't tell by holding it,
then you're an amateur.

656
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:23,360
What?

657
00:37:23,580 --> 00:37:25,033
That gun isn't loaded.

658
00:37:25,730 --> 00:37:27,944
You're not qualified
to be a bouncer. Move!

659
00:37:32,740 --> 00:37:33,740
