on the organization.

887
00:56:05,910 --> 00:56:08,673
By the looks of it, they're
doing a lot of research.

888
00:56:08,950 --> 00:56:10,550
Maybe he's a rat for the cops.

889
00:56:11,142 --> 00:56:12,142
No way.

890
00:56:12,558 --> 00:56:14,558
No way would the
cops trust a yakuza.

891
00:56:14,640 --> 00:56:17,010
But this needs a
thorough investigation.

892
00:56:18,330 --> 00:56:19,860
If he's willing to go so far,

893
00:56:21,530 --> 00:56:22,580
I have an idea too.

894
00:56:34,182 --> 00:56:37,292
I came here today to talk to
you on behalf of Tatsumura.

895
00:56:37,970 --> 00:56:41,768
So now you're going to join
me and take down Tatsumura?

896
00:56:44,970 --> 00:56:48,040
Tatsumura wants to have
a peaceful talk with you.

897
00:56:48,602 --> 00:56:49,842
I'm gonna use
this for a moment.

898
00:57:00,031 --> 00:57:01,031
Hello.

899
00:57:01,483 --> 00:57:03,678
Hey, it's me. Yeah, I'm
giving him the phone now.

900
00:57:04,566 --> 00:57:05,566
It's Tatsumura.

901
00:57:08,651 --> 00:57:09,651
Hello.

902
00:57:09,855 --> 00:57:11,584
Tojiima? It's me.

903
00:57:12,108 --> 00:57:13,948
I don't have anything to
talk to you about now.

904
00:57:14,220 --> 00:57:15,740
You might not, but I do.

905
00:57:16,920 --> 00:57:19,770
Say, would you like to
hear a pretty woman's voice?

906
00:57:19,860 --> 00:57:20,860
What?

907
00:57:22,625 --> 00:57:23,865
Would you like
to say something?

908
00:57:26,859 --> 00:57:28,459
She doesn't seem to
have anything to say.

909
00:57:29,140 --> 00:57:30,810
But you're not an idiot.

910
00:57:31,198 --> 00:57:32,598
So I'm sure you'll
back off quietly.

911
00:57:32,947 --> 00:57:33,947
Don't give in!

912
00:57:33,947 --> 00:57:35,350
All you've done
will be for nothing!

913
00:57:35,710 --> 00:57:36,710
Akiko!

914
00:57:37,750 --> 00:57:38,883
Don't worry about me!

915
00:57:39,055 --> 00:57:40,175
Don't back off for a second!

916
00:57:55,640 --> 00:57:56,640
Akiko!

917
00:58:05,508 --> 00:58:06,508
Stop!

918
00:58:08,752 --> 00:58:09,752
Got it now?

919
00:58:10,115 --> 00:58:11,115
Back off.

920
00:58:13,353 --> 00:58:14,353
Hello?!

921
00:58:15,000 --> 00:58:16,088
Hello?! Hell--

922
00:58:18,799 --> 00:58:19,799
Damn it!

923
00:58:20,710 --> 00:58:23,160
Looks like we're done here.

924
00:58:25,510 --> 00:58:27,596
Well, I'll leave you to it.

925
00:58:29,601 --> 00:58:30,601
Wait, you son of a bitch!

926
00:58:43,515 --> 00:58:44,515
Boss...

927
00:58:49,712 --> 00:58:51,774
SANRITSU INDUSTRIES

928
00:59:10,002 --> 00:59:11,385
I'm here to see Tatsumura.

929
00:59:11,502 --> 00:59:12,502
Stay out of this, thugs.

930
00:59:15,159 --> 00:59:17,297
Mr. Tojima.
He's waiting for you.

931
00:59:18,730 --> 00:59:21,040
Excuse me, but I'll
hold your things for you.

932
00:59:25,409 --> 00:59:26,409
What's up?

933
00:59:26,409 --> 00:59:27,409
Heh-heh. Wellâ¦

934
00:59:31,130 --> 00:59:32,228
- Sis!
- Don't move!

935
00:59:35,336 --> 00:59:36,676
Sorry about last night.

936
00:59:37,986 --> 00:59:40,180
I didn't mean to
make things worse.

937
00:59:41,070 --> 00:59:44,374
I just thought our discussion might
go better with a woman involved.

938
00:59:44,969 --> 00:59:45,969
Well, have a seat.

939
00:59:45,969 --> 00:59:48,370
We're not supposed to sit
down and talk to each other.

940
00:59:50,910 --> 00:59:51,910
I see.

941
00:59:53,887 --> 00:59:55,528
Well, let's hear your
answer right away.

942
00:59:58,252 --> 01:00:00,018
You'll back off,
of course, right?

943
01:00:00,600 --> 01:00:02,010
I'm not backing off yet.

944
01:00:02,510 --> 01:00:03,510
Oh...

945
01:00:04,843 --> 01:00:06,840
I guess we had it all wrong.

946
01:00:09,110 --> 01:00:11,260
We thought you had
a thing for that woman.

947
01:00:12,210 --> 01:00:14,130
So you don't care
what happens to her?

948
01:00:14,680 --> 01:00:16,790
I'd like to ask you
something first.

949
01:00:18,230 --> 01:00:20,270
Do you have the guts to
make a suicide pact with me?

950
01:00:20,620 --> 01:00:21,620
A suicide pact?

951
01:00:21,755 --> 01:00:22,755
Yeah.

952
01:00:23,126 --> 01:00:24,600
You wouldn't have the guts.

953
01:00:25,520 --> 01:00:26,940
Because you have
too many things.

954
01:00:29,170 --> 01:00:30,930
You ruined my business.

955
01:00:31,720 --> 01:00:33,110
And you even kidnapped Akiko.

956
01:00:34,020 --> 01:00:36,440
Thanks to you, I'm really
naked. I have nothing to lose.

957
01:00:37,739 --> 01:00:38,739
Not even my life.

958
01:00:40,836 --> 01:00:43,196
If anything happens to Akiko,
you can be sure I'll kill you.

959
01:00:44,040 --> 01:00:46,600
If you think being surrounded by
guns will stop me, you're wrong.

960
01:00:47,290 --> 01:00:48,440
I swear I'll get it done.

961
01:00:49,268 --> 01:00:50,268
How about it?

962
01:00:50,770 --> 01:00:51,930
Shall I try it right now?

963
01:00:53,511 --> 01:00:55,591
If you don't have the guts,
return Akiko immediately.

964
01:00:55,690 --> 01:00:57,010
Then you can fight me.

965
01:00:57,880 --> 01:00:59,800
Are you so rotten that
you can't even do that?

966
01:01:07,690 --> 01:01:09,880
Boss, I know who the spy is.

967
01:01:10,909 --> 01:01:11,909
Who is it?

968
01:01:12,530 --> 01:01:13,582
It's that bastard Kaji.

969
01:01:15,916 --> 01:01:18,674
He didn't see me and I caught
him trying to save the girl.

970
01:01:19,470 --> 01:01:21,530
I tied him up and threw
him in the basement.

971
01:01:22,746 --> 01:01:23,746
I seeâ¦

972
01:01:24,735 --> 01:01:26,260
So he was the cop's dog.

973
01:01:28,774 --> 01:01:29,992
Or was he your dog?

974
01:01:35,172 --> 01:01:36,812
I guess that was a
stupid question to ask.

975
01:01:37,970 --> 01:01:39,190
Let's ask Kaji himself.

976
01:01:40,250 --> 01:01:41,250
Show our guest the way.

977
01:01:54,260 --> 01:01:56,370
So you're a dirty rat and
you had me fooled, too.

978
01:01:57,080 --> 01:01:59,190
I'd like to know
who asked you to do it.

979
01:01:59,683 --> 01:02:02,527
I just felt sorry for the girl,
so I decided to let her go.

980
01:02:03,772 --> 01:02:05,412
I'll make you wish
that you'd talked.

981
01:02:11,091 --> 01:02:12,731
- Idiot!
- Bastard!

982
01:02:12,828 --> 01:02:13,828
Idiot!

983
01:02:16,410 --> 01:02:17,788
It's useless to beat me up.

984
01:02:17,789 --> 01:02:18,789
Useless, huh?

985
01:02:20,605 --> 01:02:21,605
Wait.

986
01:02:22,318 --> 01:02:24,118
That's some nerve you got.
Give me the pistol.

987
01:02:25,889 --> 01:02:27,123
Tatsumura, I have a request.

988
01:02:27,965 --> 01:02:29,480
You're finally
starting to understand.

989
01:02:29,480 --> 01:02:32,030
He was trying to save my girl.
I'm responsible for that.

990
01:02:33,139 --> 01:02:34,779
If you're doing this
for me, don't bother!

991
01:02:35,319 --> 01:02:36,912
I have no connection
whatsoever to you.

992
01:02:38,390 --> 01:02:41,795
Besides, he's not someone
you can negotiate with.

993
01:02:42,018 --> 01:02:43,018
I see.

994
01:02:49,298 --> 01:02:50,298
Sit him up.

995
01:02:54,840 --> 01:02:55,840
Wait.

996
01:02:57,708 --> 01:02:59,708
If you're worried about me,
mind your own business.

997
01:03:01,170 --> 01:03:05,203
I've admired men like you
since I was a kid.

998
01:03:07,120 --> 01:03:08,500
You've been my dream.

999
01:03:09,240 --> 01:03:10,240
Please.

1000
01:03:10,647 --> 01:03:11,873
Please don't destroy my dream.

1001
01:03:18,874 --> 01:03:19,874
Stop!

1002
01:03:21,430 --> 01:03:22,430
Wait.

1003
01:03:24,076 --> 01:03:25,076
Wait.

1004
01:03:25,555 --> 01:03:26,915
Finally you're ready
to come clean.

1005
01:03:28,820 --> 01:03:31,160
I don't want to die by
the hand of this beast.

1006
01:03:33,366 --> 01:03:34,366
Mr. Tojima.

1007
01:03:34,999 --> 01:03:37,740
Shoot me with your hand.

1008
01:03:39,412 --> 01:03:40,412
Please.

1009
01:03:42,822 --> 01:03:43,822
Give me the gun!

1010
01:03:44,853 --> 01:03:46,100
This is one hell of a show.

1011
01:03:46,844 --> 01:03:47,924
Let me enjoy the spectacle.

1012
01:03:50,682 --> 01:03:52,886
Come on! Come on!

1013
01:04:08,129 --> 01:04:09,129
He's dead.

1014
01:04:21,900 --> 01:04:23,520
That takes care of one of them.

1015
01:04:24,184 --> 01:04:25,997
Think the next one
through carefully.

1016
01:04:26,625 --> 01:04:27,648
Our guests are leaving.

1017
01:04:28,324 --> 01:04:29,366
Politely see them out.

1018
01:04:34,928 --> 01:04:37,799
TOJIMA BROTHERS

1019
01:04:58,539 --> 01:04:59,539
Damn.

1020
01:05:00,382 --> 01:05:01,580
They're all over the place.

1021
01:05:03,376 --> 01:05:06,420
Everyone, just hang in there.

1022
01:05:08,060 --> 01:05:09,060
But Boss--

1023
01:05:09,060 --> 01:05:10,700
If we back off, Osamu
won't rest in peace.

1024
01:05:12,374 --> 01:05:13,608
Akiko won't be pleased either.

1025
01:05:14,000 --> 01:05:15,080
But with such surveillance!

1026
01:05:15,080 --> 01:05:16,080
There's still a way!

1027
01:05:17,400 --> 01:05:19,110
We're disbanding today!

1028
01:05:20,619 --> 01:05:21,619
What?

1029
01:05:21,789 --> 01:05:23,029
The Tojima family
has disbanded?

1030
01:05:23,380 --> 01:05:24,380
Yes, I'm sure.

1031
01:05:24,492 --> 01:05:25,533
I saw it with my own eyes.

1032
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:29,294
With him still around,
we can't be too careful.

1033
01:05:29,649 --> 01:05:33,110
Why don't you get rid of all
the moonshine we have on hand?

1034
01:05:33,407 --> 01:05:35,383
Mmm. You'd better get prepared.

1035
01:05:36,530 --> 01:05:38,450
I'll have the factory
moved to the Kansai region.

1036
01:05:58,068 --> 01:05:59,148
- Shochu with cider.
- Sure.

1037
01:06:05,974 --> 01:06:06,974
Hey! How's it going?

1038
01:06:10,657 --> 01:06:11,657
What's wrong?

1039
01:06:11,914 --> 01:06:13,434
- That's weird.
- What is?

1040
01:06:13,875 --> 01:06:15,394
Look. A milk truck
at this hour?

1041
01:06:17,129 --> 01:06:18,915
If it's a courier,
it should have an escort.

1042
01:06:22,947 --> 01:06:23,987
That's it. I'm sure of it.

1043
01:06:23,987 --> 01:06:25,241
But how do we follow it?

1044
01:06:25,540 --> 01:06:27,160
Got it! I'll handle it!

1045
01:06:36,179 --> 01:06:37,632
Hey! What are you doing?

1046
01:06:37,657 --> 01:06:39,010
I'm borrowing it for a while.

1047
01:06:39,010 --> 01:06:40,755
Idiot! I'm a cop!

1048
01:06:40,755 --> 01:06:42,435
We're gonna lose 'em
if you talk like that!

1049
01:06:42,440 --> 01:06:43,443
I'll return it later!

1050
01:06:47,705 --> 01:06:49,523
There it goes!
Are you coming or not?

1051
01:06:49,819 --> 01:06:51,459
Looks like I have no choice.
I'm with you.

1052
01:07:01,415 --> 01:07:02,962
They're slowing down.

1053
01:07:04,171 --> 01:07:05,411
It's to see if we're following!

1054
01:07:05,993 --> 01:07:07,513
They're changing lanes.
I'm gonna pass!

1055
01:07:38,531 --> 01:07:39,750
Okay. Here we go.

1056
01:07:40,210 --> 01:07:41,370
Let the boss know right away.

1057
01:07:41,609 --> 01:07:43,249
I'll take a good look
at the surroundings.

1058
01:07:46,400 --> 01:07:47,400
- Hello?
- Boss!

1059
01:07:47,400 --> 01:07:49,161
- Yeah.
- We located the moonshine factory!

1060
01:07:49,507 --> 01:07:50,507
What?

1061
01:07:50,507 --> 01:07:52,267
It's in the warehouse
district at the harbor!

1062
01:07:52,420 --> 01:07:53,420
Come soon!

1063
01:07:53,430 --> 01:07:55,070
Everyone is supposed
to meet here!

1064
01:07:55,208 --> 01:07:56,248
Okay! I'll be right there!

1065
01:08:37,467 --> 01:08:38,467
You.

1066
01:08:40,077 --> 01:08:41,921
I told you I'd never
leave your side.

1067
01:08:43,038 --> 01:08:44,490
Now you owe me one.

1068
01:08:45,490 --> 01:08:47,130
Make sure the debt
won't be irrecoverable.

1069
01:09:07,830 --> 01:09:08,830
Great work.

1070
01:09:09,050 --> 01:09:10,780
Here's a map of the
area around the factory.

1071
01:09:11,270 --> 01:09:13,590
There are entrances and exits
at the front and the back.

1072
01:09:14,070 --> 01:09:15,070
Okay, I got it.

1073
01:09:15,118 --> 01:09:16,269
Let's split up and go in.

1074
01:10:18,682 --> 01:10:19,802
Everybody drop your pistols!

1075
01:10:28,975 --> 01:10:29,975
Tojima.

1076
01:10:30,991 --> 01:10:32,348
I see you were the cops' dog.

1077
01:10:33,650 --> 01:10:34,780
Who stabbed us in the back?

1078
01:10:38,810 --> 01:10:40,180
You were too careless.

1079
01:10:40,180 --> 01:10:42,610
I'm just trying to learn how to
organize the G-men next time.

1080
01:10:43,850 --> 01:10:46,200
Look, here comes the
one you want now.

1081
01:10:54,687 --> 01:10:55,687
Goro!

1082
01:10:59,000 --> 01:11:01,539
Next time pick someone who's
not greedy for money or women.

1083
01:11:01,933 --> 01:11:02,933
So...

1084
01:11:02,991 --> 01:11:04,231
Take our guests
to the basement.

1085
01:11:10,480 --> 01:11:12,400
This factory is
closed because of you.

1086
01:11:13,398 --> 01:11:16,118
If you're going to die, it might as
well be in a place with memories.

1087
01:11:16,721 --> 01:11:18,900
In one hour this place
will be nothing but ashes.

1088
01:11:19,480 --> 01:11:20,870
Along with all
of you, of course.

1089
01:11:20,987 --> 01:11:22,972
Boss. The explosives are ready.

1090
01:11:24,180 --> 01:11:25,180
Get ready to leave.

1091
01:11:26,718 --> 01:11:27,718
Tojima.

1092
01:11:28,352 --> 01:11:30,118
I told you a comeback
was impossible.

1093
01:11:32,673 --> 01:11:34,579
Never underestimate
the power of a jinx.

1094
01:11:38,290 --> 01:11:39,950
Damn it! You son of a bitch!

1095
01:11:40,313 --> 01:11:41,313
Stop pulling!

1096
01:11:41,313 --> 01:11:42,553
The debt will be irrecoverable!

1097
01:11:44,671 --> 01:11:45,671
Boss.

1098
01:11:45,900 --> 01:11:46,940
We have to do somethingâ¦

1099
01:11:49,139 --> 01:11:50,380
You can have your traitor back!

1100
01:11:51,043 --> 01:11:52,043
Damn you!

1101
01:12:00,458 --> 01:12:01,458
Damn it!

1102
01:12:02,033 --> 01:12:03,127
They tricked me!

1103
01:12:05,448 --> 01:12:07,250
Brother, I'm sorry!

1104
01:12:07,766 --> 01:12:11,573
They bribed me!
I couldn't resist!

1105
01:12:14,585 --> 01:12:15,585
I'm sorry!

1106
01:12:16,132 --> 01:12:17,442
Forgive me, everyone!

1107
01:12:42,220 --> 01:12:43,220
Goro!

1108
01:12:54,965 --> 01:12:55,965
Brother!

1109
01:13:04,652 --> 01:13:05,652
Hey, everyone hurry up!

1110
01:13:07,470 --> 01:13:08,470
Goro!

1111
01:13:19,096 --> 01:13:20,096
Damn it!

1112
01:13:21,212 --> 01:13:22,420
Let me do it.

1113
01:13:55,805 --> 01:13:56,805
I told you...

1114
01:13:58,709 --> 01:13:59,729
I told you I'm a pro.

1115
01:14:03,471 --> 01:14:04,471
Goro, hey!

1116
01:14:04,612 --> 01:14:05,612
Goro!

1117
01:14:34,446 --> 01:14:35,446
Shoot it open!

1118
01:14:39,157 --> 01:14:40,890
Damn it, we need weapons!

1119
01:14:40,969 --> 01:14:41,969
Here.

1120
01:14:44,678 --> 01:14:45,918
- What about Tojima?
- Yes, sir!

1121
01:14:45,919 --> 01:14:47,779
- Get it done quickly.
- Hey! Come on!

1122
01:14:49,780 --> 01:14:51,709
- Where are they?
- Inside! Go!

1123
01:15:24,740 --> 01:15:25,740
Go!

1124
01:15:53,840 --> 01:15:55,411
Hello? Hello?!

1125
01:16:12,473 --> 01:16:13,473
Damn it!

1126
01:16:16,625 --> 01:16:17,625
Damn it!

1127
01:16:21,820 --> 01:16:22,890
Motherfuckers!

1128
01:16:49,230 --> 01:16:51,090
- Are you ready?
- I finally got two cars.

1129
01:16:51,570 --> 01:16:52,699
Okay. Let's go!

1130
01:17:25,074 --> 01:17:26,636
That way! Huh?

1131
01:17:35,700 --> 01:17:37,114
- Hey! The back?
- We're surrounded.

1132
01:17:37,114 --> 01:17:38,114
Okay! Head for the gate!

1133
01:18:59,658 --> 01:19:00,658
Over there!

1134
01:19:02,103 --> 01:19:03,700
Good, good. Where's Tojima?

1135
01:19:10,099 --> 01:19:11,099
Go!

1136
01:19:22,510 --> 01:19:24,050
Hey! Hold on!

1137
01:19:27,780 --> 01:19:28,780
As I thought.

1138
01:19:30,292 --> 01:19:31,748
The debt was irrecoverable.

1139
01:19:34,039 --> 01:19:35,039
Kuroki!

1140
01:19:36,161 --> 01:19:37,161
Damn!

1141
01:20:36,416 --> 01:20:37,416
Tatsumura...

1142
01:20:44,187 --> 01:20:45,187
Get up!

1143
01:20:47,929 --> 01:20:48,929
Get up and move!

1144
01:21:04,395 --> 01:21:05,395
Tojima!

1145
01:21:05,985 --> 01:21:07,762
Tojima! You did a great job!

1146
01:21:07,904 --> 01:21:09,348
- Because of you we--
- Old man...

1147
01:21:11,230 --> 01:21:12,230
Three men are dead.

1148
01:21:14,270 --> 01:21:15,691
Don't say anything now.

1149
01:21:39,463 --> 01:21:41,114
What have we accomplished?

1150
01:21:44,380 --> 01:21:48,029
I feel like we've lost
more than we've gained.

1151
01:21:49,280 --> 01:21:50,280
I don't think so.

1152
01:21:51,040 --> 01:21:53,370
We did the right thing
for the first time.

1153
01:21:54,139 --> 01:21:56,860
Yeah. Even the dead
must be happy about that.

1154
01:21:59,440 --> 01:22:00,660
Let's send them on their way.

1155
01:22:18,645 --> 01:22:25,546
THE END

